Ingredients:
Turkey Mince x2
Seasoning blend
Black Pepper
1/2 Red Onion
Banana Ketchup
Scotch Bonnet Pepper Sauce
Medium Eggs x2
Slice of 1/2 & 1/2 bread
Brioche Buns
Lettuce
Tomatoes
Cheese Slices
Condiments
Frozen French Fries
Vegetable Oil
-
Method:
â€¢ Toast your slice of bread and let sit to go cold, minced/ whizz in a blender to create breadcrumbs
â€¢ In a large bowl put the turkey mince meat, breadcrumbs, seasoning blend, black pepper, banana ketchup, minced red onion, scotch bonnet pepper sauce and the eggs
â€¢ Combine well with your hands (remove all jewellery prior to carrying out this step)
â€¢ Shape into burger patties and leave to one side
â€¢ Add a little oil to a frying pan and begin by searing off the burgers (you do not have to cook them through as we will be finishing them off in the oven)
â€¢ Once all burgers have been seared place on a pre-lined baking sheet with greaseproof paper
â€¢ Bake in the oven on gas mark 4 for 15-20mins (or until cooked to your likely)
â€¢ On a separate pre-lined baking tray lined with greaseproof paper place your French fries and bake in the oven for 15-20mins
â€¢ Remove both the burgers and fries from oven and allow to rest for 3-5mins
â€¢ This step is optional - Lightly toast your burger buns
â€¢ Prep your lettuce, tomatoes and condiments
â€¢ Now for the fun part...Time to assemble your burgers!
